title: For Sale/Trade:  MKE 380 auto Concealed Carry gun
postcontent: This is a nice MKE 380 auto pistol. It's a 7+1 capacity.  That's 1 more then the ruger/taurus/diamondback/kel-tec/hellcat style pocket pistols.This is a variant to the Walther PPK pistols. James Bond style. It breaks down and functions just like a PPK/Makarov.  Quick and easy to brake down and clean. This ones made in Turkey and imported by Firearms Center of Victoria Texas. Its small and could be used as a concealed carry pistol but large enough to be comfortable in you hand and accurate. The PPK design features a fixed barrel, meaning the barrel stays attached to the frame when the slide is removed. This ads to the accuracy of the gun. Most pocket pistols or even alot of full size pistol barrels flop around when the slide is open. That means when you fire the gun the barrel could tilt upward while the bullet is leaving the gun. This gun is in very nice condition. Blue slide with a brownish color frame. Comes with a nice leather belt holster. Like I say perfect concealed carry gun. Reliable and accurate so you can carry it and not have to worry if its going to work when you need it. It features a safety/decocker that allows you to keep a round in the chamber with out having to worry. I buy sell and trade, so let me know what you have. I prefer text REDACTED. and let me know which gun you interested in, I have several for sale. email REDACTED I'm asking $300 with the holster.

Burris 3-9x40mm Fullfield II Rifle Scope w/ Burris 10x32mm Landmark Binoculars gives you a full spot-and-shoot package! This value package from Burris includes the Burris 3x-9x 40mm Fullfield-II Riflescope and the Burris Landmark 10x32mm Binoculars.

The Burris Fullfield II Rifle Scope has a one-piece main tube and eyepiece, Burris envied steel-on-steel adjustment system, and HiLume multi-coatings on every single air to glass lens surface. The Burris FullField-II Scope is even more forgiving for eye position, is a little shorter, and a good bit lighter. The magnification ring and eyepiece have been made into one solid unit requiring only two seals rather than three. To change magnification, simply turn the entire eyepiece. Burris Fullfield 2 Scope eliminated most of the potential leak paths in the eyepiece/power ring area and sealed the remainder with special quad seals instead of O-rings. The adjustment system has been moved to improve mounting options and the European-style adjustable eyepiece requires no locking mechanism. The Ballistic Plex reticle has a lower vertical crosshair with small ballistic lines that automatically compensate for bullet drop from 100 to 500 yards for many common cartridges. The Burris Fullfield-2 Riflescope is lighter, better sealed, and has a relocated adjustment system compared to the original Burris Fullfield.

The Burris Landmark Binoculars combine light weight, fully coated lenses and water resistant, fogproof construction. These Burris Binoculars also include a tough rubber armor coating and twist-up eyecups. Top all this off with a neck strap, carrying case, a full year warranty and a very affordable price and you have yourself a synonym for optical value.

Waterproof: All Burris optics are proven to be absolutely waterproof. Each scope is submerged in water with a temperature of 50° C. The extremely hot water transfers its heat to the scope and the internal nitrogen expends 100% testing assures quality. Each scope is filled and purged at least 24 times with high quality, laboratory grade dry nitrogen. Each nitrogen cycle absorbs airborne and residual surface moisture that is evacuated from the scope. Burris uses specially made quad seals to provide double insurance against leakage.
Fog proof: The nitrogen contained in the scope is of high quality (ultra dry, laboratory grade nitrogen), ultra pure and ultra clean. To be sure that all airborne moisture and surfaces moisture within a scope is evacuated, testing consists of 24 cycles of pressurizing the scope and then subjecting it to a vacuum. The tests are both cost & time intensive.
Shock proof: Burris scopes are subjected to extreme recoil tests. An impact machine is used to measure and duplicate the recoil pulse acceleration and duration. This machine has been calibrated and verified by an independent laboratory to replicate the wave frequencies and shock impulses that a scope is subjected to.
Ballistic Plex reticle - with a basic crosshair reticle, calculating hold-over is a mix of art, science and just plain luck, which is why Burris developed the Ballistic Plex reticle. The key is the copyrighted lower vertical crosshair. With most common hunting cartridges, a shooter can use the reticle to compensate for bullet drop and aim dead-on at targets from 100 to 500 yards out. title: For Trade:  STAG ARMS 6.5 Grendel AR15..
postcontent:
Stag Arms AR15 in 6.5 Grendel. Comes as pictured, I will include 2 mags, 1 25 and 1 10.
This is a very hot round and it isnt cheap. It has a YHM phantom muzzle break and its a flat top m4 style.


The 6.5mm Grendel design goal was to create an effective 200-800 yard AR-15 magazine length loaded cartridge for the AR-15 platform that surpassed the performance of the native 5.56 NATO / 223 Remington cartridge. Constrained by the length of the 5.56 mm NATO round, the Grendel designers decided to use a shorter, larger diameter case for higher powder volume while allowing space for long, streamlined, high ballistic coefficient (BC) bullets. Firing factory loaded ammunition loaded with bullets ranging from 90 to 129 grains (5.8–8.4 g), its muzzle velocity ranges from 2,500 ft/s (760 m/s) with 129- and 130-grain (8.4 g) bullets to 2,900 ft/s (880 m/s) with 90 gr (5.8 g) bullets (similar in velocity to a 5.56 mm 77-grain (5.0 g) round).

title: For Sale/Trade:  Browning BDA 380
postcontent:
This is a very good condition Browning BDS 380 with a extra magazine. 
Manufactured in 1980. This has been sitting in the safe for years with only a few rounds through it.
 The Browning BDA 380 pistol was introduced in 1980 or so as a compact and lightweight pistol for police and civilian use. The gun was manufactured in Italy under contract from FN Herstal (Belgium) and marketed as FN model 140DA (in Europe) or Browning BDA 380 (in USA). Some sources said that BDA 380 is a copy of Beretta 84, but close inspection shows some differences (i.e. Beretta 84 has frame mounted safety while BDA 380 has slide mounted safety). The manufacture of the BDA 380 was ceased circa 1997. It was adopted by Belgian police.

The BDA 380 is a blowback operated, double action semi automatic pistol. It has aluminium alloy frame and steel slide. Ambidextrous slide mounted safety switch disconnects the trigger from the hammer when engaged. The pistol featured low profile fixed sightst and was available in either polished steel or blued finish, with wooden grip panels.

This is the Hi-Standard Supermatic match pistol with the 4.5" weighted barrel and the 6.75" barrel, 3 magazines, weights and filler strip included. It has been sitting in the safe for years. These are what they use in the Olympics to shoot with and what other match grade guns are judged by.
This same gun was $1100 on Gun Broker and not in as good of shape.
The up scale model, Supermatic, incorporated a rib dovetailed to the top of the barrel and a dovetail slot on the bottom of the barrel for mounting balance weights. .22 LR caliber pistol with 10 shot magazine. Heavy weight round barrel; blued finish; adjustable sights; brown plastic thumb rest grips. Grooved front and back straps on frame. Available with 4.5"or 6.75" barrels or combination with both barrels. Ribbed barrels and provisions for weights. A 2 oz and a 3 oz weight were provided with this model as was a filler strip for when the weights were not used.

The PT22 is a .22LR semi-automatic pistol produced by Taurus and features an 8+1 round capacity magazine. The PT22 is often viewed as a Taurus copy of the Beretta 21 Bobcat due to having a similar "tip up" barrel. In fact this small pistol is very different in design and function from the Beretta. The PT22 is a cast steel frame and slide, manufactured in Florida, USA. It has a spur-less hammer, and a long but smooth double action only (DAO) trigger. The "tip up" barrel is useful in that the first round may be chambered directly into the barrel, and the operator does not have to "pull back" or "rack" the slide.
